1. Heat a LARGE wok over high heat, add and swirl coconut oil. Add shallots and onion, sautee 2-4 minutes until browning. Add ginger, garlic, and chili. Stir-fry 2 minutes. While stir-frying add dry spices: coriander, cumin, turmeric, white pepper, and bay leaves.\
\
2. Add stock plus chickpeas, carrot, tofu, snow peas (optional squash, potato if using), stir well. Add coconut milk and bring to a gentle boil.\
\
